<br>
In fact, he looks a bit vampyric to me.<br>
<br>
Maybe he was infected by a coterie and the force field is designed to keep him IN, not keep us OUT.  It's plausible, since I believe one of the quests in Seru involves finding a spy who turns out to have been infected with vampirism.  Since the coterie and Seru are natural enemies in Luclin, it would seem to fit in with the emerging storyline.<br>
<br>
That might explain why you take some positive and negative Seru faction hits at once.  Maybe some factions in S Seru are keeping this knowledge from the other factions.<br>
<br>
Though I'm probably wrong, it is still an interesting thought, is it not?<br>
